Title: New Treehouse Course: Basic Math for Data Analysis



We’re excited to announce Basic Math for Data Analysis, a new instruction in Python from Megan Amendola and Jennifer Nordell!
This 25-minute course covers some essential math concepts and how to program them using Python. It’s the perfect primer for those things you may have forgotten since school, or never have learned to begin with. This course will get you up to speed!

In Basic Math for Data Analysis, you’ll form (or reestablish) a foundation in:

Maximum
Minimum
Mean
Mode
Median
Percentage
Order of Operations

Catch up on your basic math and build the foundation you’ll need in order to start learning data analysis principles. Let’s get started!
